From a7f3d84f908be33f0d38aecc3309c0688736243a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: psyclyx <me@psyclyx.xyz>
Date: Fri, 3 Apr 2026 00:28:53 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] su: Add daemon mode for seccomp-safe root access

Redesign su as a client/daemon pair. The daemon runs as root
(started by init), so it has no seccomp restrictions from Zygote.
Apps connect to the daemon over a Unix socket at /dev/socket/su_daemon,
pass their stdin/stdout/stderr via SCM_RIGHTS, and the daemon
forks+execs the requested command.

This fixes su failing with "setgid failed: Operation not permitted"
when called from Zygote-forked app processes, which have seccomp
filters that block setuid()/setgid() syscalls.

Wire protocol:
  1. Client sends stdin/stdout/stderr fds via SCM_RIGHTS
  2. Client sends: target_uid, target_gid, argc, then each arg
  3. Daemon verifies caller UID via SO_PEERCRED against whitelist
  4. Daemon forks, sets uid/gid, execs command
  5. Daemon sends back exit code

Change-Id: Id0463e5ba4cba271c3fd74fb03285c162f4f7296
