+/*
+ * su client/daemon — works from Zygote-forked app processes.
+ *
+ * The daemon runs as root (started by init), so it has no seccomp
+ * restrictions. The su client connects to the daemon over a Unix
+ * socket, passes its stdin/stdout/stderr via SCM_RIGHTS, and the
+ * daemon forks+execs the requested command.
+ *
+ * Usage:
+ *   su --daemon              Start daemon (called by init)
+ *   su [WHO [COMMAND...]]    Client mode (connects to daemon)
+ */
+
